    en: "New York requires health insurance plans to cover hearing aids for children under age 18. The coverage mandate runs through three parallel insurance code sections — Insurance Law 3216(i) for individual policies, 3221(l) for group policies, and 4303 for HMO coverage. The mandate covers a pair of hearing aids every 3 years, costs of molds, batteries, and related audiology services, and repairs. Plans must cover both bone-conduction and air-conduction hearing aids when medically necessary. Cost-sharing is subject to the plan's deductibles and coinsurance but may not be more restrictive than for other durable medical equipment. Medicaid and Child Health Plus cover hearing aids for kids without the age-18 cap, under program-specific rules."
